the use of computers in engineering classroom instruction .won april -, the computer committee of thecollege of engineering, university of michigan, which acts as a steering committee for the ford foundationproject on the use of computers in engineering education, held a special conference to discuss certaintimely topics pertinent to the ford project.  this report contains a condensed transcription ofthe key ideas offered by the conference attendees on selected topics. cacm october, katz, d. l.ca jb march ,   : pm